{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PNt2biQWMrX84uvP38yrP9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture!\n\n**The `ingress-gateway` service:** This is an ExternalName service in the `demo` namespace that points to `ingress-nginx-controller.ingress-nginx-2.svc.cluster.local`. This means traffic going to `ingress-gateway.demo.svc.cluster.local` will be routed to the controller in the `ingress-nginx-2` namespace.\n\n**What needs to happen:**\n1. Create the `ingress-gateway` ExternalName service in the `demo` namespace\n2. Create/update the `demo-app` ingress to have `ingressClassName: ingress-2` and host `class.example.com`\n3. Set up the `ingress-2` IngressClass pointing to the controller in the `ingress-nginx-2` namespace\n\nLooking at the existing setup, only the `nginx` class was created during the initial stage. For this to work, I need to create the `ingress-2` IngressClass that references the `k8s.io/ingress-nginx-2` controller running in the `ingress-nginx-2` namespace.\n\nNow I should check what the stage_01 agent actually did to understand what the demo Ingress currently looks like and what needs updating.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2131,"cache_read_input_tokens":39936,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2131},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"29f1f8b2-c5f2-4710-84f5-1e85f07074a3","uuid":"067f62e4-83a8-4219-8740-7314d99ed5b4","request_id":"req_011Cc6c8ZoDTcQHPeST7voyU"}
